  <prompt>
    Add the getViewUrl() method to SpeDocumentViewer's BffClient to enable
    real-time document preview without the 30-60 second cache delay that
    getPreviewUrl() has. Port the implementation from SpeFileViewer.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    SPAARKE platform developer. Expert in TypeScript and PCF development.
    Follow ADRs strictly.
  </role>

  <goal>
    SpeDocumentViewer BffClient has a getViewUrl() method that returns
    real-time preview URLs with checkout status, matching the SpeFileViewer
    implementation.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      SpeDocumentViewer currently uses getPreviewUrl() which calls the BFF
      /api/documents/{id}/preview-url endpoint. This endpoint uses Graph's
      Preview action which has a 30-60 second cache. SpeFileViewer uses
      getViewUrl() which calls /api/documents/{id}/view-url - this uses
      driveItem.webUrl for near real-time viewing without cache delay.

      For email-to-document automation, newly created .eml files need to be
      viewable immediately without waiting for cache to expire.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/client/pcf/SpeFileViewer/control/BffClient.ts</file>
      <file>src/client/pcf/SpeDocumentViewer/control/BffClient.ts</file>
      <file>src/client/pcf/SpeDocumentViewer/control/types.ts</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="project">Method signature must match SpeFileViewer implementation</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Return type must include checkoutStatus for lock indicators</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-022">Use platform-provided React (already compliant)</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
